# Optional API Key for Enhanced Security
#
# DEFAULT BEHAVIOR (No configuration needed):
# API authentication is DISABLED by default for zero-friction local development.
# The server is protected by CORS (localhost only) and network binding (127.0.0.1).
#
# To enable API key authentication (recommended for LAN exposure):
# PIPER_API_KEY=your-custom-secret-key
#
# Example usage with custom key:
# 1. Set PIPER_API_KEY=my-secure-random-key below
# 2. Update the API_KEY in your extensions/integrations to match
# 3. All requests must then include the key:
#    - Header: X-API-Key: my-secure-random-key
#    - Or URL parameter: ?api_key=my-secure-random-key
